<br>
Your assumption is that the FT would be an overriding difference between the two. However, it isn't really, mana regen being the way it is, a lot of us with PoP already don't run out of mana as it stands. If you don't run out of mana, more FT basically has no impact. Spells would be a good thing to differentiate by, but people tend to whine a bit too much about that. As it is now, the main differences are in amount of hp (this can make a huge difference in PoP fights), total amount of mana, and resists. Changing the FT cap, while nice, will have little impact though. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
