<br>
There is a cast effect similar to emp robe that does 8 regen that we can see on Lucy.<br>
<br>
Better mana preservation is also to be expected, and already available on gloves.<br>
<br>
Also, you can assume a minimum mana regen for a wizard in Elemental gar to be standing + FT15 + lunar whisper (emp robe a bit rare for some guilds) + Harvests + Flappy + Epic + KEI = 53 strict minimum. Usually more around 80. 5 more on FT cap is 6-10% more mana regen.<br>
<br>
The mana pool pre-Time is already increased by 20-30ish percent with PoP.<br>
<br>
Also, wether using Iceflame with Ice Spear and Destruction or SoS, there is a big improvement in both DPS and damage per mana.<br>
<br>
Additional AAs of course make things better.<br>
<br>
Add all these things together, and even in an xp group with a tank who can hold aggro (Maelin's legs help on that of course) you'll find that at the end of PoP a well geared wizard will probably sustain double the DPS he did at the end of Luclin. Sure, another 6-10% (depending on buffs available) from increase in the FT cap would be nice, but it's not a big enough difference to bother me not having it...<br>
<br>
