<br>
-AEs that reduce your ability to fight. very broad<br>
-aggro! this is one of the largest wizard limiting factors, in some ring events with multiple offtanked targets you can rotate between them but this is not so on single targets<br>
-mana. in the luclin era prenerf, fights were so long(camp 10 charge keys just for a 40 min fight woot) that you'd be quite close to your sustained dps.in a 45 min fight a 5k mana pool would amount to 11/tick in compare.<br>
<br>
For wizards there's a maximum attainable dps, and a maximum for the given aggro. I think some spellcast subtly type items - ie Subversion of Ro would 20% deaggro fire - would be good to loot... aggro as a limiter really limits the benefit you can get out of your mana/ft items. when the luclin caster candies were set forth, I think they made a much bigger difference than they do now in POP.<br>
<br>
mana rate in the days of yore really was the way caster dps was improved but I think things have changed a bit now. aggro and mana are both limiting factors for a wizard. what is my opinion on how to make goodies in potime to look forward to? Don't shove the high powered focus effects onto just 1 or 2 items. give some variety to stuff, like the flowing thought effect could be found on nearly every slot in luclin. ie you got xegony wand orb of sun and seashell but it turns out that the imagined subtly effects are in those slots - ouch.<br>
<br>
I think:<br>
higher spell haste<br>
subtly<br>
more dmg<br>
<br>
focus items would be the way to go with us for starters. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rombusmindspire>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 6720<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/13/03 6:42:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25924.topic&index=52>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: mm</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>-AEs that reduce your ability to fight. very broad<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I can't think of a single PoP or Luclin AE that has ever prevented me from doing large ammounts of damage.  Every AE is easily avoidable for casters.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>-aggro! this is one of the largest wizard limiting factors, in some ring events with multiple offtanked targets you can rotate between them but this is not so on single targets<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Aggro is a limiting factor, but obviously it goes without saying it would be totally imbalacing if it wasn't possible to overaggro.  If you watch what you're doing though aggro is (for the most part) easily avoided.<br>
