I'll use numbers (again) for the 80% figure:<br>
<br>
if you have 84/tick mana and 6300 mana pool(good elemental equip), then you'd have to find the difference of 1260 mana over the course of the fight.<br>
(mna pres of 7.5% from the average + ~21% from skill = 28.5% mana save?):<br>
<br>
draught of e'ci: 2.1 + 2.25 seconds, 182mana. drains mana at a rate of 41.8 mana/sec and 84/tick is 14 mana/sec. This leaves us with a difference of 27.8 mana/sec drained.<br>
1260/27.8 = 45.3 seconds<br>
<br>
does this sound about right(this is off some surely)? to illustrate that point, for the draught of e'ci(a random nuke I figure you may refer to) the whole mana rate et cetera reduces the rate at which your mana can be drained chain casting this to 66%.<br>
<br>
