I don't think you see my point. How is it going to help grouping if you already are nuking at the agro limit and not running out of mana? I could have FT100 and the amount of damage per hour I do in an exp group is not going to change one iota. The same is true for most wizards with 5k+ mana and FT15. I can post logs from hours of exp groups with damage to the tune of 300k per hour. For that matter, you can go see some logs of that type of damage in the library, wizards have been limited by agro quite a while now. The only way to do a significant amount of damage would be to lower the amount of agro our nukes generate. The only difference the FT can has is how long it takes to get back to FM AFTER the group stops fighting which is basically irrelevant anyway.<br>
<br>
I will concede that it would make us better soloers because we would be able to take targets with more HP and the down time between targets would be a lot less. However, I would argue that wizards are already on the verge of being overpowered soloing as it is. It is not hard for wizards to solo mobs with over 80khp and even quad kite mobs with over 50khp. I really doubt that SOE intended for us to get 72% of an AA in a single quad kite or 1.5aa per hour solo. More FT would just increase these numbers because the FT cap basically only limits wizards when agro is not pertinent. In cases where agro control matters, agro is the limiting factor in how much damage we do, not mana regen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=istari@graffeswizardcompilation>Istari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/14/03 5:43:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25924.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hm</span><hr size=1> it depends on what kind of grouping you have. ever seen a sotlc+ aggro weap equipped paladin aggro? It's a lot, I have even used draught of thunder in chain nukes to bring down a mob w/ telekin that only a paladin and I were on and kill it without taking aggro off him. granted, he likely didn't take interrupts and was fully buffed... but it's still a lot of aggro(and other factors definately worked into this). In many group situations, we're limited by aggro. This is generally with wars tanking. Hybrids have superior aggro to this, however. In truth it helps in some group situations but not all. Though I admit that I do not group much, I always tended to be consitently fighting mobs. one number for a pala